## 8. Business Rules

### Rule 1 — Auto Assign Network Incidents

| Property  | Value                         |
|-----------|-------------------------------|
| Table     | Incident                      |
| When      | Before Insert and Update      |
| Condition | Category = network            |

**Logic:**
- Queries sys_user table for user with user_name = 'mike.agent'
- Sets assigned_to field to Mike Agent's sys_id
- Every Network ticket is automatically routed to Mike Agent

---

### Rule 2 — Set Default Priority

| Property  | Value              |
|-----------|--------------------|
| Table     | Incident           |
| When      | Before Insert only |
| Condition | Priority is empty  |

**Logic:**
- Checks if priority field is nil/empty
- If empty, sets priority = 3 (Moderate)
- Ensures every ticket always has a priority value

---

### Rule 3 — Keyword Based Priority Escalation (Bonus Feature)

| Property  | Value                    |
|-----------|--------------------------|
| Table     | Incident                 |
| When      | Before Insert and Update |
| Condition | Always runs              |

**Logic:**
- Reads the Description field text
- Converts to lowercase for comparison
- Scans for urgency keywords:
  - "urgent", "critical", "immediately", "asap" → Sets Priority = 1 (Critical)
  - "high", "important", "severe" → Sets Priority = 2 (High)

**Example:**
```
Description: "My internet is not working urgently, please fix asap"
Result: System detects "urgently" and "asap" → Auto sets Priority = Critical
```

