## 12. SLA (Service Level Agreements)

SLAs define the maximum time allowed to resolve a ticket based on its priority.
The timer starts automatically when a ticket is created.

| SLA Name                    | Priority   | Duration | Target     |
|-----------------------------|------------|----------|------------|
| High Priority Incident SLA  | 2-High     | 4 Hours  | Resolution |
| Medium Priority Incident SLA| 3-Moderate | 8 Hours  | Resolution |
| Low Priority Incident SLA   | 4-Low      | 24 Hours | Resolution |

**SLA Status:**
- ✅ SLA Met — Ticket resolved within the time limit
- ❌ SLA Breached — Ticket not resolved within the time limit

