## 14. Complete End-to-End Scenarios

### Scenario 1 — Network Incident with Urgent Keyword

```
Step 1 : John User opens a new Incident form
Step 2 : Types Description = "internet not working urgently"
Step 3 : Business Rule 3 runs → detects "urgently"
         → Auto sets Priority = 1 (Critical)
Step 4 : Client Script runs → Priority changed to Critical
         → Alert popup: "🚨 Critical Priority Ticket!"
Step 5 : UI Policy runs → Priority = Critical
         → Description field becomes MANDATORY
Step 6 : John selects Category = Network
Step 7 : John submits the form
Step 8 : Business Rule 1 runs → Category = Network
         → Auto assigns ticket to Mike Agent
Step 9 : Auto number generated → SINC0001001
Step 10: SLA timer starts → Must resolve in 4 hours
Step 11: Notification sent → John receives email with ticket details
Step 12: Mike Agent logs in, sees the ticket assigned to him
Step 13: Mike resolves the issue → sets State = Resolved
Step 14: Ticket → Closed ✅
```

---

### Scenario 2 — Service Request for Laptop

```
Step 1 : John User creates a new Service Request
         Request Type = Laptop
         Requested For = John User
Step 2 : Flow Designer trigger fires → record created
Step 3 : Flow Step 1 → Approval request sent to manager
         Approval Status = Pending
Step 4 : Flow Step 2 → Email sent to John
         "Your service request is pending approval"
Step 5 : Manager reviews and approves the request
         Approval Status → Approved
Step 6 : IT Agent fulfills the request
         Delivery Date is set
Step 7 : Laptop delivered to John ✅
```

